rComments: I had him for Linear Algebra and initially thought he was a good prof. However, after the tests and exams, I have changed my mind. His exam was extremely difficult and unlike anything we had seen in class. It was unfair and shocking. Try to avoid. If you do have him really try to know your stuff as the exam may shock you.
Great professor, wish I had him for every course

I would highly recommend him for Statistics. His lecture notes are very good so u don't even need to take notes and his assignments are easy marks. The mid term and final were fairly easy too, as long as u spend some time practicing past exams you shouldn't have any issues getting an A.

This class is not supposed to be as hard as he made it out to be. He posts his notes online, which are disorganized and handwritten. During the lectures all he does is read off his notes and copying them on the board. Also, his notes have a lot of mistakes which gets confusing since you cannot trust his notes. Also, his heavy accent does not help.

This course wasn't supposed to be that hard, but the professor made it very difficult. He reads entirely off the slides, which he posts online anyway, making class very boring. The notes were also full of mistakes.
Excellent professor.
a very very great prof
Too many mistakes he makes in his lecture notes that confuse you!
very hard to understand and moves way too fast. acted like we should already know what were doing rather than teaching. midterms were somewhat fair but the final was not fair.

He goes very fast for a course that is a makeup credit from high school math. a lot of us struggle in math and that's why we have to take it and it makes it harder...i find he talks like we should already know what we're doing rather than actually teaching us what to do
Great prof,
Excellent professor
Very Good professor

Bentoumi was a caring professor. Despite this, his lectures were really boring and he read off the slides. He talked quietly so it was hard to understand him. He would erase the board before you finished copying the solutions down which was annoying. Overall, just do the past midterms and finals and you'll do fine.
Good professor.
Best professor I had in the semester. He works hard, cares about his students.

Bentoumi seems a bit severe in the beginning, but he is quite caring about his students. He works hard, but his English and accent can be a bit of struggle in class. Plus, he makes a lot of mistakes in lectures, although he does manage to have a laugh about it. 1 midterm and final weren't too bad. Overall, nice guy, but very average prof.

The whole point of a math professor is to take math language and translate it into non-math language so that you can understand it. This guy just reads off the notes in sub-par English. Attending class often felt like a total waste of time. At least his exams were very similar to the practice ones he posted.
Easy A. Do all the assignments and practice tests, and the exams are really similar. Lectures are dry and not necessary to attend except to get the answers to the problems

This class has weekly homework which is an easy way to boost your grades. He speaks REALLY SOFTLY, so make sure you sit near the front. Try and find midterms from previous years online because he reuses the same questions every year.

This prof never spoke loud enough in class. He skips over the material quickly and the homeworks don't make sense. He'll put things you've never seen on your midterms. . If you ask him a question in class that seems stupid to him, he will call you out. And if you ever mess around in this class, he will hold it against you forever and embarass you.
Superbe professeur. Les évaluations sont représentatives de la matière vue en cours.

Great professor, really cares about his students and does everything in his power to make sure you get the best grade possible. Does go over some concepts pretty quickly, but DGDs make up for it. Gives a little homework, which prepares you really well for the following midterm. Exams reflect the material very well, you know what to expect.
Great prof, wants his students to succeed. Talk  with him and he will actually try and help you out!

Best professor I had in the semester. Such a great guy, always friendly and makes the class fun. Super helpful and a generous marker. He wants his students to succeed and actually cares about them, which is not only refreshing but gives you motivation. Deserves an award for his awesomeness.
Pretty easy going teacher. Midterm and homework assignments were fair.
Good teacher !
No passion for his subject, mumbles, can't understand what he's saying at all. He's bland and its difficult to understand his thought process.
